# UI UX Pro Max

For design, layout, visual polish, or UX improvements on this site:

1. **Read** `.cursor/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/SKILL.md` and follow its workflow.
2. **Run** the design-system command from the repo root (use `python` on Windows):
   `python .cursor/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/scripts/search.py "<product> <industry> <keywords>" --design-system -p "Copper Skies" -f markdown`
3. **Supplement** with `--domain ux`, `--domain typography`, or `--stack nextjs` / `--stack html-tailwind` as SKILL.md describes.
4. **Synthesize** with the **existing brand**: dark cinematic sections, orange accent, current font stack—do not replace the whole theme from a generic palette unless the user asks.
5. **Verify** the Pre-Delivery Checklist at the end of SKILL.md (contrast, focus, motion, no emoji icons, etc.).

Repository reference: [ui-ux-pro-max-skill](https://github.com/nextlevelbuilder/ui-ux-pro-max-skill).
